# Raw video sources never get committed — only the optimised
# transcodes under `public/hero/` ship to Vercel. If you've dropped a
# 31 MB phone-shot `.mov` straight into `public/`, this rule keeps it
# out of the deploy artifact while the file still sits on your disk.
public/*.mov
public/*.MOV
public/*.avi
public/*.mkv
public/*-source.*
# Belt-and-braces: any single video file > a few MB anywhere in
# `public/` is almost certainly an un-optimised source we don't want
# to ship. Keep this loose to the file pattern; we DO want
# `public/hero/home.mp4` (the optimised output) to be committed.
public/source-*

